-- JA Solar, Hong Kong's GCL-Poly Sign 10-Gigawatt Solar-Power Supplies Deal
-- B y   T o d d   W h i t e
-- 2010-12-02T11:37:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-02/ja-solar-hong-kong-s-gcl-poly-sign-10-gigawatt-solar-power-supplies-deal.html
JA Solar Holdings  Co., a Chinese
maker of solar-power components, said it will buy 10 gigawatts
of “high-quality” polycrystalline wafers and polysilicon
products from  GCL-Poly Energy Holdings Ltd.  during a five-year
period from January 2011 to December 2015, in a filing. The
contract with Hong Kong-based GCL-Poly has a price-adjustment
mechanism, JA said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Todd White  at 
 twhite2@bloomberg.net  